\Phi\!\left(\frac{\beta_k - \rho x_i}{\sqrt{1-\rho^2}}\right)
-
\Phi\!\left(\frac{\beta_{k-1} - \rho x_i}{\sqrt{1-\rho^2}}\right).
}
The returned estimate maximises the log-likelihood
\deqn{
\ell(\rho) = \sum_{i=1}^{n}\log \Pr(Y_i = y_i \mid X_i = x_i, \rho)
